The paper focuses on designing optimal incentive mechanisms for mobile crowdsensing, which involves analyzing the participation level of mobile users and the optimal incentive mechanism of the crowdsensing service provider. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper takes into account the social network effects from the underlying mobile social domain, indicating that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to mobile networks and wireless communication, which could place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the incentive mechanism, which could suggest that it belongs to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper explores the impact of social structure information on the incentive mechanism, which could place it in the Social Computing (cs.SOC) sub-category.
